582
00:45:49,625 --> 00:45:51,916
a completely invincible sword which they

583
00:45:51,916 --> 00:45:53,666
would call Jue.

584
00:45:53,666 --> 00:45:54,875
But, it was cursed.

585
00:45:54,875 --> 00:45:56,333
Whoever tried to forge this sword

586
00:45:56,333 --> 00:45:58,416
would die a sudden and violent death.

587
00:45:58,416 --> 00:46:00,708
The sword's spirit was
uncontrollably fierce.

588
00:46:00,708 --> 00:46:03,291
- But, isn't a fierce sword a good sword?

589
00:46:03,291 --> 00:46:05,208
- True but a man should
never be controlled

590
00:46:05,208 --> 00:46:09,625
by the sword he uses or he
will lose all his humanity.

591
00:46:09,625 --> 00:46:11,500
- Of course, Father.

592
00:46:11,500 --> 00:46:13,666
- Our ancestors considered
the evil of the sword

593
00:46:13,666 --> 00:46:16,791
was too great so they buried
it inside a stone cavern

594
00:46:16,791 --> 00:46:19,250
before any more trouble
could be brought upon them.

595
00:46:19,250 --> 00:46:21,000
They decreed that none
of their descendants

596
00:46:21,000 --> 00:46:23,125
should learn how to use it and each year

597
00:46:23,125 --> 00:46:26,083
they made sure to worship the
sword to protect the family.

598
00:46:36,333 --> 00:46:37,500
- [Voiceover] Master, the Emperor says

599
00:46:37,500 --> 00:46:39,541
Sword Worship Villa was
planning a rebellion.

600
00:46:39,541 --> 00:46:40,750
The army's here already.

601
00:46:43,958 --> 00:46:45,875
- I should never have
worked for the Emperor.

602
00:46:45,875 --> 00:46:47,041
(shouting)

603
00:46:49,750 --> 00:46:50,833
- Master, Master.

604
00:46:50,833 --> 00:46:52,125
- Kay, I don't have much time.

605
00:46:52,125 --> 00:46:53,458
I know Jue loves you.

606
00:46:54,583 --> 00:46:57,291
But, your martial arts is
derived from a negative power

607
00:46:57,291 --> 00:47:00,250
while Jue's skills are derived
from a positive energy.

608
00:47:01,166 --> 00:47:05,166
For the sake of Jue, promise
me you'll never marry him.

609
00:47:05,166 --> 00:47:06,833
Now hurry and get him outta here.

610
00:47:10,208 --> 00:47:11,625
Get outta here.

611
00:47:26,125 --> 00:47:26,875
- Master.

612
00:47:29,791 --> 00:47:31,125
- Father.

613
00:47:31,125 --> 00:47:33,083
I know where I can find
the Flame Kylin's blood

614
00:47:33,083 --> 00:47:35,041
to awaken the Sword Jue.

615
00:47:35,041 --> 00:47:37,083
And soon, I'll get revenge.

616
00:47:38,500 --> 00:47:43,250
(somber music)

617
00:47:48,625 --> 00:47:49,666
You killed my father.

618
00:47:50,708 --> 00:47:52,541
You destroyed my home

619
00:47:52,541 --> 00:47:55,041
and you even desecrate
the land of my ancestors?

620
00:47:55,041 --> 00:47:56,708
You despicable emperor.

621
00:47:58,041 --> 00:47:58,833
(epic music)

622
00:47:58,833 --> 00:48:00,041
(yelling)

623
00:48:52,500 --> 00:48:56,208
(rumbling)

624
00:48:56,208 --> 00:49:00,583
(struggling)

625
00:49:15,625 --> 00:49:17,791
It truly is an evil sword.

626
00:49:17,791 --> 00:49:18,916
Just what I need.

627
00:49:30,375 --> 00:49:32,416
(exploding)

628
00:49:35,541 --> 00:49:37,791
(thunder booming)

629
00:49:38,791 --> 00:49:40,333
- From the Conquerer's Clan.

630
00:49:40,333 --> 00:49:42,291
If we let him stay here,
it'll just bring us trouble.

631
00:49:42,291 --> 00:49:44,166
- But he killed Conquerer.

632
00:49:44,166 --> 00:49:46,208
That severs any ties he had with the clan.

633
00:49:47,291 --> 00:49:50,625
- Mistress, can you really
bet all our lives on it?

634
00:49:50,625 --> 00:49:53,041
(thunder booming)

635
00:49:53,041 --> 00:49:55,833
- What I'm about to do isn't
anything personal, Wind.

636
00:49:55,833 --> 00:49:57,708
We're trying to avoid any trouble here.

637
00:49:59,333 --> 00:50:01,041
(fighting)

638
00:50:01,041 --> 00:50:02,125
(glass breaking)

639
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:05,666
- Master Wind, please, spare his life.

640
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:25,166
(monkey chattering)

641
00:50:25,166 --> 00:50:26,166
That fire monkey.

642
00:50:28,583 --> 00:50:29,958
- Mud Buddha?

643
00:50:29,958 --> 00:50:31,291
- Ah, this is fate.

644
00:50:34,500 --> 00:50:37,666
Master Wind, it seems fate has
brought us together, again.

645
00:50:40,208 --> 00:50:42,083
(thunder booming)

